---
title: Taverna Steak & Dilly Potato Wedges with Roasted Veggies & Tzatziki
description: This week, we’re taking meat and potatoes on a 30-minute pleasure cruise to the Mediterranean with a spice-rubbed steak you’ll sear to a deep brown in the pan, then finish with butter. Meanwhile, two sheets of veggies are roasting in the oven: one with dill-sprinkled potato wedges—destined for crispy outsides and creamy insides—and the other with oregano-kissed zucchini and red onion. You’ll plate up all of this deliciousness, then drizzle with creamy, tangy cucumber yogurt sauce (aka tzatziki), packed with garlic, fresh lemon juice and zest, and even more herbaceous dill.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6595102c050f2b642e9a282d-69e8f703.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6595102c050f2b642e9a282d.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Southern Europe
nutrition:
  calories: 590 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 680 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/taverna-steak-dilly-potato-wedges-6595102c050f2b642e9a282d
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Pick and roughly chop fronds from @Dill{¼%ounce}(fronds picked and chopped). Trim and halve @Zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Halve and peel @Red Onion{1}(peeled and halved); slice into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon}, half the dill, @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Toss zucchini and onion wedges on a separate baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, @Dried Oregano{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While veggies roast, trim and finely dice @Mini Cucumber{1}(trimmed and finely diced). Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}.

Pat @Ranch Steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with half the @Mediterranean Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}. TIP: For perfect timing, start steak when potatoes have 10-12 minutes left!

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. (If steak is browning too quickly, lower heat!)

Add @Butter{1%tablespoon} to pan; stir until melted, then spoon over steak until coated, ~{10-15%seconds}.

Transfer steak to a #cutting board{} and let rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

While steak rests, in a #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, lemon zest, @Yogurt{4%tablespoon}, @Crème Fraîche{4%tablespoon}, remaining dill, juice from one lemon wedge, and as much garlic as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice steak against the grain.

Divide steak, potato wedges, and zucchini-onion jumble between plates. Serve with remaining lemon wedges and tzatziki on the side.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.